description:
This is a 16 minute workout called 'Baseball Row' from the channel Mike Dostal.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Endorphin Wave and The Groove Session vibe.
The The Endorphin Wave vibe means Elevated energy, feel-good movement, steady build. This is especially good for When you want a challenging but steady burn. The The Groove Session vibe means Fun, fluid, expressive, completely in the moment. This is especially good for Days when you want to move intuitively and just vibe..
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Dive into the essence of summer with Mike on the Charles River in this 15-minute Sweat. Experience the perfect mix of steady jogs and sprinting runs as you alternate between 22 and 28 strokes per minute. Mike brings the heat with his unique take on American baseball, mixing in humor and confusion as he navigates through the quirks of the sport while keeping your heart rate up. Max rhythm: 28, Format: Intervals....
